<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Chandra_7th</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-09-22 04:57:46</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Give the Dwarf upstairs in the Hogcaller's Inn in Freeport about 3 plat worth of muffins and your faction will be plenty high enough.  That is how I did it.  ( You get the muffins from the bakery next to the Monk's guild in the same zone. )</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Molian</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-11-08 22:36:52</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Ok I'm not aware of all of this muffin crap but I will give you the complete quest including faction improvement. there are 3 things you need for the falchion 1)The Black Heart of Dvinn(ambassador Dvinn) 2)Blue Orc Head(Orc Prophet) 3)Brawn's Crate(Brawn). You may hear that you have to do the orc runner quest first which is bull...trust me I've done this quest twice(My first falchion was deleted during server boot and the generous folks at verant gave me a LONGSWORD ...damn pussy boy assholes). Anyway to start this quest go to Crushbone and go to the tower of the castle...more likely than no there will be a high-level group there camping Ambassador Dvinn, they want his faction and his Dragoon dirk...all you need to do is ask if you can loot the heart.If you are over 25 then you can probably kill him yourself but I'm not sure...never tried. Once you have the heart keep waiting for the Orc Prophet who also spawns in the tower im not sure of his level but id guess 14-16. He drops the blue orc head which means you are roughly half way there(the crate is much harder than you think). Now head to the docks in Butcher Block and hop on the boat. Once the boat zones to Ocean of Tears look of the right side of the boat (if you are facing the front) and wait till you see an island (the first island to your right once you zone to OOT) and jump off the boat to that island . Now once you get to that island run to the opposite side and you'll see another island with three sirens. Now i strongly suggest you find a level 25+ druid friend to camp Brawn because at 4am or 5am in the morning(game time that is) instead of sirens Brawn the Ogre and 2 dragoons who are level 22 each and Brawn is 23. Have the druid harmonize the 2 dragoons which means that if he casts a fire burst at Brawn they won't attack also. Once you kill Brawn loot the 20lbs crate off of him and you are ready to get the falchion. Now in order to get good faction head to Greater Faydark and beat down some skeletons for bone chips and offer a plat to newbies for a stack of them and when you have about 150 bone chips go to the cleric guildmaster of felwithe and give them to him. this should get you pretty good faction...to see if the faction is good enough go to Lord Jyleel in the paladin guil basement and hail him and follow his quotes until he says that either you have not proven yourself to the guild (which means you need to give the cleric guild master more bone chips) or he will tell you about the falchion...if hes says that give him the heart, the head, and the crate and receive the falchion of koada'vie. This is a pretty nice sword I got it at level 17...and now keep it in the bank for corpse retrievals (Im now equipping BIBS). OK I'll stop rambling...if you found this post to be helpful and informative post something...i like to know i made someones day a lttle easier.   </font></td></tr></table>
